mmmkay ! I had a fun weekend XD 
 First on Saturday night I went and hung out at Sparkles with Kelly,Lindsay, and Ashton. Soo fun.xD Kelly called me at like 6:30 and was like "Get your ass down here,we're surrounded by annoying preppy people and they're playing crappy music!" So down there I went. I didn't actually go skating,but still had fun.  We played a bunch of arcade games and then played Laser Tag. Unfortunately our team lost cuz we had a bunch of lil kids on our team.And the other side had one of the guys working there playing with them ! (RECOUNT !) We got them to play Shakira's Hips Dont Lie and we all danced for a bit.We generally had a good time.. *nods*wanna do it again but with a bigger group of ppl.

Then on Sunday My mom and I picked Kelly up at Martins where she workds now,and she dropped us off at Regal 22 on the EW Connecter and we saw You Me And Dupree.xD She made me try a drink from Smoothie King..Not too bad. We also hung out at CJ Games for a bit. Saw Tripodie(Shawn, and no not Tiffy's shawn) we also saw Randal and Boberts Brother..who I cant remember his name for the life of me right now..>< I know he used to be Millies BF ( Who I found out moved to South Dakota recently) I found out that they're still hiring up there so sometime this week after 5 I have to go up there and fill out an application. w00tage for the job hunting again.

And then today I went to Acworth Beach with my mom,sis and her two kids.My aunt kathy was already up there with my cousins timmy and brandon and my nephews Marcus and Skyler. We had lots of fun playing,although I didn't plan on getting in the water..which I did.XD but the downside of that..*whines and points to her shoulders* I Gots Sunburn !!! It huuuurts and that crappy Aloe gel stuff doesnt work >< But still.I had fun ! I wanna do it again,this time with sunscreen..*nod nod*

Well I went to a doctor about me being sick yesterday. She told me I should go and get some blood work done... She said theres a chance that I could have PCOS...and since theres a history of diabetes in my family that theres a chance I could have diabetes...

As much as I hate needles..The thought of having diabetes or PCOS makes it seem even worse... I know I should get this done for my health, to make sure if there is anything wrong with me that it gets fixed sooner rather than later.  But just thinking of my grandmother and her diabetes... She had to give herself insulin shots every day. She had to check her blood sugar every day,which meant she had to stick her fingertips for blood samples... I dont want that to be me...

I mean, its bad enough being 17 and overweight in this day's society. Im depressed enough as it is..Now for some doctor to say theres a chance i could have diabetes...God i hope I dont have it..I hope I get lucky and Don't have it..
